---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Signature Kitchen Suite Repair Los Angeles | SKS ThinQ & Sous Vide Specialists";
const description = "Expert Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS) appliance repair in Los Angeles. Built-in sous vide, Wine Cave Technology, ThinQ diagnostics, Free-Zone induction. LG platform expertise. Same-day service. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Signature Kitchen Suite Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-signature-kitchen-suite-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "SKS Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"SKS Pro Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"SKS Built-In Sous Vide Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"SKS Column Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"SKS Wine Cave Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"SKS Dishwasher Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"SKS Wall Oven Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does Signature Kitchen Suite appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most SKS repairs run $185-$620. Common fixes like an igniter, temperature sensor, door gasket, or sous vide circulation pump are on the lower end. Control board or sealed system work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Signature Kitchen Suite made by LG?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS) was launched in 2016 as LG's luxury appliance brand. SKS uses the LG ThinQ platform, LG's linear compressor technology in refrigerators, and LG's smart diagnostics infrastructure. Our deep LG repair experience applies directly to SKS diagnostics — we know the ThinQ error code system, linear compressor behavior, and LG platform electronics that underpin every SKS appliance."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair the built-in sous vide on an SKS range?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The SKS built-in sous vide module circulates water at precise temperature for sous vide cooking. Common failures: the circulation pump loses efficiency (water circulates weakly), the temperature sensor drifts, or the heating element fails. We diagnose the sous vide module as a distinct subsystem, layer by layer."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Wine Cave Technology and how does it fail?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Wine Cave Technology is SKS's dual-zone wine preservation system with specific humidity control and vibration isolation. Common failures: zone temperature drift (usually a zone sensor, not the sealed system), humidity system fault, and vibration isolation mount degradation. We test each zone and the humidity system independently before any sealed system diagnosis."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you use ThinQ Care diagnostics when servicing SKS appliances?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. ThinQ Care is LG's AI-driven remote diagnostic system that monitors SKS appliances and flags issues. We read ThinQ Care diagnostic history as part of every SKS service call — operational logs often tell us exactly which component is failing before we open the unit. If your ThinQ app sent you an alert, mention it when you call."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My ProSteam wall oven stopped steaming — is it the steam generator?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Almost certainly scale, not the generator. LA water at 250-400 ppm builds scale in the ProSteam circuit 2-3x faster than standard maintenance intervals assume. Manual deep descaling resolves the vast majority of ProSteam failures. We also reset the descaling interval to match LA water hardness on every ProSteam service call."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .firsts-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .first-card { background: #161616; padding: 18px 14px; text-align: center; }
  .first-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .first-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .first-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-lg { border-color: #a50034; background: #fff0f4; }
  .tip-lg .tip-label { color: #a50034; }
  .tip-steam { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-steam .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-sousvide { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-wine { background: #5a2a7a; }
  .tag-smart { background: #2a7a4a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .firsts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon-Sat 8am-8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Signature Kitchen Suite Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        SKS Repair.<br/>
        <span>Sous Vide. Wine Cave.</span><br/>
        ThinQ Platform.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Signature Kitchen Suite is LG's luxury lab — the brand that put sous vide inside a range, Wine Cave Technology inside a wine cellar, and ThinQ AI inside every appliance. We service every SKS innovation, same day, with the LG platform expertise that makes diagnosis fast and accurate.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">ThinQ</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Platform Expert</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">SKS Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Built-In Sous Vide Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Wine Cave Technology Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">ThinQ Care Diagnostics</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About Signature Kitchen Suite</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">LG's Luxury Lab. Launched 2016. Already Consumer Reports Most Reliable.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Signature Kitchen Suite (SKS) launched in 2016 as LG's dedicated luxury appliance brand — and moved faster than almost any luxury brand in history from launch to critical recognition. Within a few years, Consumer Reports rated SKS among the most reliable appliance brands on the market. The reason is the LG foundation: decades of electronics engineering, linear compressor technology refined through millions of units, and the ThinQ AI platform that brings diagnostics and smart connectivity to every SKS appliance.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      What SKS brought that no other luxury brand had: built-in sous vide directly in the range cooktop — an industry first. Free-Zone induction that treats the entire cooktop surface as one cooking zone. Wine Cave Technology that replicates traditional wine cellar conditions with humidity and vibration control. A 48" pro range that combines gas, induction, and sous vide on a single cooktop. These are genuine innovations — and they require specific technical knowledge to service correctly.
    </p>
    <div class="firsts-grid">
      <div class="first-card">
        <div class="first-icon">🫙</div>
        <div class="first-label">Industry First</div>
        <div class="first-name">Built-In Sous Vide</div>
      </div>
      <div class="first-card">
        <div class="first-icon">🔵</div>
        <div class="first-label">SKS Innovation</div>
        <div class="first-name">Free-Zone Induction</div>
      </div>
      <div class="first-card">
        <div class="first-icon">🍷</div>
        <div class="first-label">SKS Innovation</div>
        <div class="first-name">Wine Cave Technology</div>
      </div>
      <div class="first-card">
        <div class="first-icon">📷</div>
        <div class="first-label">SKS Innovation</div>
        <div class="first-name">Gourmet AI Camera</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block tip-lg" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🔴 SKS = LG Platform — Our Direct Advantage</div>
      <div class="tip-text">Signature Kitchen Suite is built on LG's electronics platform — ThinQ ecosystem, linear compressor technology, and LG control board architecture. We are one of the highest-volume LG repair services in Los Angeles. That experience transfers directly to SKS: ThinQ error codes, linear compressor behavior, LG inverter boards are all familiar territory. Faster diagnosis, more accurate parts prediction, better first-visit completion rates on SKS calls.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every SKS Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All Signature Kitchen Suite models — pro ranges, column refrigerators, Wine Cave Technology, wall ovens, dishwashers. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>
    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🫙</div>
        <div class="service-name">Pro Range &amp; Sous Vide Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">SKS professional ranges — 30", 36", and the 48" that combines gas burners, Free-Zone induction, and built-in sous vide on a single cooktop. The sous vide module circulates water at precision temperature (0.1°F accuracy). Its circulation pump, heating element, and temperature sensor are distinct components we diagnose as a separate subsystem. The Ultra-High 23,000 BTU burners and Ultra-Low simmer zones also have specific igniter and valve configurations.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: sous vide pump failure · sous vide temperature drift · Ultra-High igniter failure · gas valve · induction zone fault · oven temperature · convection fan · ProSteam fault · Smart Knob error</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍷</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wine Cave Technology Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">SKS's dual-zone wine preservation system controls both temperature and humidity simultaneously while maintaining near-zero vibration levels — replicating a traditional wine cellar. The humidity injection system has no equivalent in standard wine refrigerators. When humidity levels drift or vibration damping degrades, preservation conditions change in ways that affect wine quality. We service all Wine Cave Technology components including the humidity system.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: zone temperature drift · humidity system fault · vibration isolation degradation · door gasket · temperature sensor · compressor · fan motor · ThinQ connectivity · LED lighting</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Column Refrigerator &amp; Freezer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">SKS column refrigerators and freezers — including the 48" French door with 5-mode convertible drawer. The linear compressor from LG provides quieter operation and more precise temperature control. SKS's Craft Ice sphere ice maker is also a specific service point — the sphere-forming mechanism requires different service than standard ice makers.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: linear compressor anomaly · not cooling · convertible drawer mode fault · Craft Ice sphere maker · water dispenser · door gasket · condenser service · ThinQ temperature alerts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven &amp; ProSteam Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">SKS wall ovens — single, double, and steam-combination models with ProSteam and the Gourmet AI camera that monitors food browning. The ProSteam system uses a water injection circuit — LA hard water at 250-400 ppm builds scale in the steam circuit faster than standard maintenance intervals assume. We descale and recalibrate the steam system on every SKS steam oven service call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: ProSteam scale buildup · Gourmet AI camera fault · ProConvect fan · temperature sensor · door gasket · self-clean lock · heating element · control board</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Dishwasher Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">SKS fully integrated dishwashers running at 37 dBA — among the quietest on the market. At 37 dBA, any noise from an SKS dishwasher is immediately noticeable and diagnostic. A grinding sound means pump debris. A rhythmic clicking means spray arm contact. We diagnose by noise character before opening the unit. LA hard water scale in the spray circuit is addressed on every SKS dishwasher call.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: noise (diagnostic at 37 dBA) · not cleaning · not draining · spray arm scale · door latch · control board · water inlet · heating element · ThinQ error codes</div>
      </div>
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔵</div>
        <div class="service-name">Free-Zone Induction Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">SKS Free-Zone induction treats the entire cooking surface as one flexible zone — cookware of any size or shape can be placed anywhere. Free-Zone failures require diagnosis at the surface management board level, not individual zone inverters as with standard induction. The diagnostic approach is completely different from standard induction cooktop repair.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: zone not recognized · surface not heating · E-codes · surface management board · temperature inconsistency · flex zone boundary errors · control board · glass surface assessment</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block tip-steam" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">📱 ThinQ Care — Read the Logs Before We Arrive</div>
      <div class="tip-text">SKS's ThinQ Care AI monitoring logs operational data continuously — compressor run times, temperature trends, cycle counts, and anomalies. We read ThinQ Care diagnostic history as part of every SKS service call. A refrigerator that's been logging compressor run-time increases for three weeks before the owner noticed temperature drift tells us to check sealed system efficiency and condenser before component-level diagnosis. If your ThinQ app has sent alerts — note them before calling. It helps us arrive with the right parts.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">SKS Innovations — What They Are and How They Fail</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Every SKS industry first is a subsystem with its own failure modes. Here's what each system does and what breaks — and why LG platform knowledge matters.</p>
    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Built-In Sous Vide Module</strong> — The sous vide unit inside an SKS pro range cooktop circulates water at plus or minus 0.1°F precision. It has three independent components: a circulation pump (most common failure — loses flow rate), a precision temperature sensor (drifts), and a heating element. Most general technicians treat sous vide failure as a range electronics issue. We diagnose the sous vide module as a standalone subsystem with its own parts path.</li>
        <li><strong>Free-Zone Induction Technology</strong> — Standard induction has 4-5 fixed zones with independent inverters. SKS Free-Zone treats the entire surface as one zone. A Free-Zone failure is a surface management board issue, not an individual zone inverter fault. The diagnostic approach is completely different from standard induction cooktop repair.</li>
        <li><strong>Wine Cave Technology Humidity System</strong> — Beyond temperature and vibration control, SKS Wine Cave Technology actively manages relative humidity — mimicking a traditional limestone wine cellar. The humidity injection system uses a water reservoir and ultrasonic or evaporative system to maintain specific RH levels. This has no equivalent in standard wine refrigerators and requires specific component knowledge to service.</li>
        <li><strong>LG Linear Compressor</strong> — SKS column refrigerators use LG's linear compressor — a single reciprocating piston driven directly by a linear motor, with no crank mechanism. Linear compressors fail differently: anomalies typically show as increased run time before any temperature change. ThinQ Care often catches this weeks before the owner notices. Our LG linear compressor diagnostic experience applies directly.</li>
        <li><strong>Gourmet AI Camera (Wall Oven)</strong> — SKS's interior oven camera monitors food browning in real time. Camera failures are usually lens fogging from condensation (steam oven environment) or LED illumination degrading. Neither requires oven disassembly — both are accessed through the camera module service panel.</li>
        <li><strong>Smart Knobs with Built-In Timers</strong> — SKS range knobs incorporate LED timer rings and touch sensors. Smart Knob failures trace to the knob's electronics board or the connection to the range control system — not the gas valve the knob controls. We separate the knob electronics failure from the range function failure in every Smart Knob diagnostic.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🫙 Sous Vide Pump — The Failure Nobody Expects</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">The most common sous vide failure is the circulation pump losing flow rate — it still runs but moves less water, creating temperature stratification in the bath. Owners notice uneven cooking results and assume a temperature sensor issue. We test pump flow rate directly before checking the sensor. A weak pump needs replacement — recalibrating the sensor won't fix uneven circulation. Most sous vide calls resolve in a single visit.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#1a0a16; border-color:#7a2a5a; margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#c85aa0">💧 LA Hard Water + SKS ProSteam</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">SKS ProSteam wall ovens inject steam for humidity-assisted cooking. LA water at 250-400 ppm is far harder than the European baseline SKS's standard descaling interval assumes. Scale accumulates in the water inlet, steam generator, and distribution circuit 2-3x faster. SKS's automatic descaling cycle isn't sufficient at LA water hardness — manual deep descaling resolves the vast majority of ProSteam failures. We reset the descaling reminder to match LA water hardness on every ProSteam service call.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common SKS Failures in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🫙 Sous Vide Cooking Unevenly</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Circulation pump flow rate loss — the pump still runs but moves less water, creating temperature gradients in the bath. Owners notice uneven cooking results before identifying the source. We test pump flow rate directly. Pump replacement resolves this in most cases — sensor recalibration alone won't fix uneven circulation.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-sousvide">Sous Vide</span>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ ProSteam Not Generating Steam</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Scale buildup in the steam circuit — LA hard water at 250-400 ppm accumulates scale 2-3x faster than standard maintenance intervals assume. Almost always scale, not a component failure. We deep descale the full steam circuit and recalibrate the descaling reminder to LA water hardness on every ProSteam call.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍷 Wine Cave Zone Temperature Drift</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Zone-specific temperature sensor failure — the Wine Cave sealed system remains functional. Zone drift (one zone off while the other holds temperature) is consistently a zone-level fault. We test each zone's sensor, damper, and humidity system independently before any sealed system assessment.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-wine">Wine Cave</span>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">📱 ThinQ App — Appliance Offline or Error</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">ThinQ connectivity module failure or firmware anomaly. Many offline reports resolve with a specific power cycle sequence — no parts needed. True module failure requires replacement. We test the reset sequence first. ThinQ error codes logged in the app history often tell us exactly what physical component is failing.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-smart">ThinQ</span>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔵 Free-Zone Induction Area Dead</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Surface management board failure — a section of the Free-Zone surface stops recognizing cookware. Unlike standard induction, Free-Zone uses a shared surface management board coordinating all coil segments. We test the management board circuit for the affected area — this is a distinct diagnosis from standard induction zone repair.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">❄️ Refrigerator Linear Compressor Anomaly</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">LG linear compressor efficiency degradation — the compressor runs longer cycles than normal without matching temperature change. ThinQ Care often logs this weeks before any temperature drift. We check ThinQ operational history first on every SKS refrigerator call — if the compressor has been over-cycling, condenser cleaning resolves most cases without sealed system work.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

