<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">09 — FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Signature Kitchen Suite Repair FAQ</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is Signature Kitchen Suite made by LG?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. SKS launched in 2016 as LG's luxury appliance brand. It uses the LG ThinQ platform, LG's linear compressor technology, and LG's electronics architecture throughout. Our extensive LG repair experience transfers directly to SKS — the platform, error codes, and component families are familiar territory.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">My SKS sous vide is cooking unevenly — what's wrong?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Almost certainly the circulation pump losing flow rate. The pump still runs but moves less water, creating temperature stratification in the bath. We test pump flow rate directly before anything else on sous vide calls. Sensor calibration doesn't fix poor circulation — the pump needs replacement. We carry SKS sous vide pump components and resolve most calls in a single visit.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">My ProSteam wall oven stopped steaming — is it the steam generator?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Almost certainly scale, not the generator. LA water at 250-400 ppm builds scale in the ProSteam circuit 2-3x faster than standard maintenance intervals assume. Manual deep descaling resolves the vast majority of ProSteam failures. We also reset the descaling interval to match LA water hardness on every ProSteam service call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is Wine Cave Technology and how is it different from a standard wine cooler?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Wine Cave Technology controls temperature, humidity, and vibration simultaneously — replicating a traditional limestone wine cellar. Standard wine coolers control only temperature. The humidity system actively maintains specific RH levels — this has no equivalent in other residential wine coolers and requires specific service knowledge. We service all three systems on every Wine Cave call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can you service Free-Zone induction cooktops?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — and Free-Zone diagnosis is different from standard induction. Standard induction has independent inverter boards per zone. Free-Zone uses a shared surface management board coordinating all coil segments. When an area of Free-Zone stops working, we diagnose the surface management board — not individual zone inverters, and not the glass surface (which most companies misidentify as the cause).</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Does SKS's 3-year warranty affect your service?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">We service SKS appliances both in and out of warranty. During the warranty period we coordinate with SKS's Concierge team for covered repairs. For out-of-warranty appliances we provide same-day service with OEM parts — often faster than the warranty channel. Many SKS owners call us specifically because they need service today, not within 5 days.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

